<AUTHOR>kathy</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>This is the first Lexus I have owned and couldn't be happier. I only drove about 800 miles, but there isn't anything I seriously dislike about the vehicle. All of the necessary features are great and the ride is beautiful. I tend to be a leadfoot and this car has not let me down, although the handling is a little light. I test drove 14 different cars, seriously researched 26, and have always bought American previously. The price was great, $8,000-$10,000 below domestic competitors in its class with similar features. Needless to say, this was a big consideration when purchasing. The dealership was A+. Give it a try-you'll fall in love!!</TEXT>
<FAVORITE>fit and finish, audio, keyless ignition, safety</FAVORITE>
